Mets Release Second Baseman Castillo With $6 Million Left on His Contract

-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 
2011-03-18T15:42:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/mets-release-second-baseman-castillo-with-6-million-left-on-his-contract.html
The  New York Mets  released second
baseman Luis Castillo, a .290 career hitter who batted .235 for
the team last season.  Castillo, 35, was acquired by the Mets from the  Minnesota
Twins  in 2007. He appeared in 86 games last season. He had one
year left on his contract that will pay him $6 million.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  